==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Exequy
<hw>Ex"e*quy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Exequies</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L. <ets>exequiae</ets>,
<ets>exsequiae</ets>, a funeral procession, fr. <ets>exsequi</ets> to
follow out: cf. OF. <ets>exeques</ets>. See <er>Exequte</er>.]</ety>
<def>A funeral rite (usually in the plural); the ceremonies of burial;
obsequies; funeral procession.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>But see his <qex>exequies</qex> fulfilled in Rouen.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Exercent</ent>⟦br⟧
